    "valid": true,
    "description": "App Service Plans provision compute resources (CPU, memory, scaling) for one or more web apps. Even when applications on the plan generate little traffic, the plan continues to incur full hosting costs.  \n\nThis Azure Benchmark workflow runs across **all selected subscriptions and selected regions**, analyzing plan-level usage to detect **under-utilization** (CPU and memory consistently below 40%) and flag them as opportunities for **downsizing** or **consolidation**.\n\n## How It Works  \n\n- Enumerate all **App Service Plans** (`Microsoft.Web/serverfarms`) across all selected subscriptions and regions.  \n- For each plan:  \n  1. Pull the last **14 days** of the following metrics:  \n     - **`CpuPercentage`** (peak)  \n     - **`MemoryPercentage`** (peak)  \n  2. Evaluate utilization thresholds:  \n     - If both **CPU < 40%** and **Memory < 40%**,  \n       - Mark the plan as **under-utilized**.  \n  3. Compare against the current SKU (e.g., P1v3, S2, I3) to suggest **smaller tiers** where applicable.  \n\n- For every under-utilized plan discovered:  \n  - Attempt to determine the current hosting cost of the plan.  \n  - Calculate potential savings based on recommended SKU downgrade.  \n  - Insert a record in the **Opportunities** list for tracking and automated follow-up within the Azure Benchmark scope.  \n\n## Required Azure Permissions  \n\n- `Microsoft.Web/serverfarms/read`  \n- `Microsoft.Insights/metrics/read`  \n- `Microsoft.Resources/subscriptions/resourceGroups/read`  \n- `Microsoft.Consumption/usageDetails/read`  "
  },
